e swimmers for just 12 months, was kept secret from the swimming community, and the actions of the World Anti Doping Agency have again been brought in question, The Australian reported yesterday.\", \"from\": 1028, \"to\": 1296, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1095, \"end\": 1102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.5788909149498058, \"rank\": 0.6007963795315263, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1200, \"end\": 1224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"World Anti Doping Agency\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 1262, \"end\": 1276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1939239859230478e-29, \"text\": \"The Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The positive drug results\", \"from\": 1028, \"to\": 1053}, {\"ngram\": \"a subsequent ban\", \"from\": 1059, \"to\": 1075}, {\"ngram\": \"just 12 months\", \"from\": 1116, \"to\": 1130}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimming community\", \"from\": 1153, \"to\": 1175}, {\"ngram\": \"the actions\", \"from\": 1181, \"to\": 1192}, {\"ngram\": \"question\", \"from\": 1252, \"to\": 1260}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Australian metropolitan media carried front page stories on the development this morning, mocking the 'bizarre' Chinese claims with headlines like \\\"Hamburglers with lies,\\\" \\\"Playing silly burglers,\\\" \\\"Would you like lies with that?\\\"\", \"from\": 1298, \"to\": 1528, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1298, \"end\": 1308, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"score\": 0.9994284916307933, \"rank\": 0.0005701829480013055, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\"}, {\"begin\": 1410, \"end\": 1417, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.5788909149498058, \"rank\": 0.6007963795315263, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"front page stories\", \"from\": 1336, \"to\": 1354}, {\"ngram\": \"the development\", \"from\": 1358, \"to\": 1373}, {\"ngram\": \"headlines\", \"from\": 1430, \"to\": 1439}, {\"ngram\": \"Hamburglers\", \"from\": 1446, \"to\": 1457}, {\"ngram\": \"lies\", \"from\": 1463, \"to\": 1467}, {\"ngram\": \"silly burglers\", \"from\": 1479, \"to\": 1493}, {\"ngram\": \"lies\", \"from\": 1512, \"to\": 1516}]}, {\"sentence\": \"and \\\"Beefgate.\\\"\", \"from\": 1529, \"to\": 1544, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"WADA and World Aquatics accepted the Chinese explanation that \\\"it was probably contamination from a lunch comprising hamburgers and fries and a soft drink at a restaurant near their training base at the National team facility in Beijing,\\\" and took no further action.\", \"from\": 1546, \"to\": 1812, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1583, \"end\": 1590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.5788909149498058, \"rank\": 0.6007963795315263, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1775, \"end\": 1782, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_China\", \"score\": 0.9999986177377199, \"rank\": 7.883058848615687e-07, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid